20to%20fight%20for%20affordable%20housing.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42b78b360acd489560d126%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222128%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Zohran%20Mamdani's%20central%20campaign%20promises%20was%20to%20fight%20for%20affordable%20housing.%3Cp%3ESelcuk%20Acar%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENYC%20Mayor%20Zohran%20Mamdani's%20rent%20freeze%20for%20stabilized%20apartments%20starts%20in%20October%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECritics%20argue%20the%20rent%20freeze%20could%20degrade%20apartment%20quality%20and%20raise%20market-rate%20rents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESubmit%20an%20inquiry%20to%20check%20if%20your%20apartment%20is%20rent-stabilized%20via%20the%20NY%20State%20Homes%20agency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Zohran%20Mamdani's%20signature%20campaign%20promises%20is%20officially%20coming%20to%20fruition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City's%20Rent%20Guidelines%20Board%20voted%207-1%20on%20June%2025%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzohran-mamdani-wants-to-freeze-rents-heres-why-its-controversial-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efreeze%20rents%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20one-%20and%20two-year%20leases%20for%20roughly%201%20million%20rent-stabilized%20apartments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rent%20freeze%20comes%20as%20many%20New%20Yorkers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypical-new-yorker-age-income-salary-occupation-rent-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estruggle%20to%20find%20affordable%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20expensive%20cities.%20Supporters%20see%20the%20policy%20as%20a%20way%20to%20address%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20by%20preventing%20housing%20costs%20from%20rising.%20Through%20Business%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fcost-of-the-city%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECost%20of%20the%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%2C%20we've%20spoken%20to%20New%20Yorkers%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20a%20living%20in%20the%20city%20and%20the%20financial%20pressures%20they%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20living%20in%20a%20rent-stabilized%20apartment%3F%20We'd%20like%20to%20hear%20from%20New%20Yorkers%20about%20how%20rising%20costs%2C%20taxes%2C%20repairs%2C%20or%20housing%20policies%20have%20affected%20you.%20If%20you're%20willing%20to%20share%20your%20experience%2C%20contact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amros%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emros%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20chaos%20of%20the%20approval%20process%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmamdani-rent-freeze-new-york-city-apartments-official-income-chart-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20celebrations%20and%20a%20resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20here's%20what%20tenants%20need%20to%20know%20about%20how%20the%20freeze%20will%20work%20and%20how%20it%20could%20impact%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd6880cb-ab77-45db-a973-bc71de4e37c7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20the%20rent%20freeze%20takes%20effect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rent%20freeze%20for%20the%20roughly%2040%25%20of%20NYC%20rental%20housing%20that%20is%20rent-stabilized%20will%20impact%20one-%20and%20two-year%20leases%20that%20start%20on%20or%20after%20October%201%2C%202026%2C%20up%20until%20September%2030%2C%202027.%20Eligible%20leases%20signed%20or%20renewed%20between%20those%20two%20dates%20will%20be%20automatically%20subjected%20to%20the%20rent%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20lease%20is%20renewed%20before%20this%20date%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-rent-prices-landlords-tenants-homebuying-apocalypse-apartment-glut-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20regulations%20accepted%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Rent%20Guidelines%20Board%20as%20of%20June%202025%20will%20apply.%20This%20includes%20a%203%25%20allowed%20annual%20adjustment%20for%20one-year%20leases%20and%20a%204.5%25%20allowed%20adjustment%20for%20two-year%20leases.%20These%20regulations%20have%20been%20in%20place%20since%20October%201%2C%202025%20and%20will%20continue%20until%20September%2030%2C%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city's%20Rent%20Guidelines%20Board%20will%20vote%20again%20next%20year%20to%20determine%20rent%20adjustments%20for%20leases%20after%20September%2030%2C%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22107c0b5e-d073-4f59-a24f-f78b5ebd1a18%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20find%20out%20if%20your%20apartment%20is%20rent-stabilized%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERent-stabilized%20apartments%20are%20usually%20in%20buildings%20built%20between%201947%20and%201974%2C%20though%20some%20newer%20buildings%20are%20also%20included%20because%20they%20received%20specific%20tax%20benefits%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhcr.ny.gov%2Foffice-rent-administration-ora%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOffice%20of%20Rent%20Administration%20(ORA)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20designation%20limits%20%26quot%3Brent%20increases%2C%20guarantees%20lease%20renewals%2C%20and%20protects%20tenants%20from%20eviction%20except%20as%20allowed%20by%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20check%20if%20you%20live%20in%20a%20rent-stabilized%20apartment%20is%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fportal.hcr.ny.gov%2Fapp%2Fask%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubmitting%20an%20inquiry%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20ORA%2C%20a%20government%20agency%20part%20of%20the%20New%20York%20State%20Homes%20and%20Community%20Renewal%2C%20the%20State's%20affordable%20housing%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20here%2C%20you%20can%20request%20your%20official%20apartment%20rent%20history%20or%20a%20form%20asking%20if%20your%20apartment%20is%20rent-stabilized.%20A%20response%20should%20be%20sent%20within%2020%20business%20days.%20If%20you%20believe%20you%20are%20being%20improperly%20charged%2C%20you%20can%20seek%20legal%20assistance%20or%20submit%20an%20overcharge%20complaint%20to%20the%20ORA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2240523c29-f51d-42de-aff2-19639674243a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20rent%20freeze%20could%20affect%20landlords%20and%20market-rate%20apartments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20the%20policy%20said%20the%20rent%20freeze%20could%20impact%20landlords'%20ability%20to%20maintain%20the%20quality%20of%20these%20rent-stabilized%20apartments.%20As%20landlords%20face%20higher%20operating%20costs%20and%20inflation%2C%20critics%20say%20the%20inability%20to%20raise%20rents%20could%20lead%20them%20to%20cut%20costs%20and%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20maintain%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArpit%20Gupta%2C%20a%20public%20member%20of%20the%20Rent%20Guidelines%20Board%20and%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20NYU%20Stern%2C%20voted%20against%20the%20freeze%20and%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.city-journal.org%2Farticle%2Fnew-york-rent-freeze%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%20published%20Friday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20long-term%20condition%20of%20these%20rent-stabilized%20buildings%20is%20%26quot%3Btroubling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFreezing%20their%20rents%20while%20their%20expenses%20remain%20uncapped%20is%20therefore%20a%20threat%20to%20their%20long-term%20financial%20viability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BResidents%20might%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20low%20rents%2C%20but%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20being%20trapped%20in%20units%20that%20no%20longer%20fit%20their%20needs%2C%20and%20with%20few%20alternatives%20and%20steadily%20deteriorating%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20freeze%20only%20impacts%20rent-stabilized%20apartments%2C%20which%20means%20rents%20on%20market-rate%20apartments%20are%20not%20directly%20affected%2