E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBaby%20boomers%20are%20having%20some%20second%20thoughts%20about%20the%20whole%20%26quot%3Btill%20death%20do%20us%20part%26quot%3B%20thing.%20Instead%20of%20waiting%20for%20someone%20to%20land%20in%20a%20coffin%20to%20go%20their%20separate%20ways%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20the%20courthouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-boost-longevity-4-minutes-daily-exercise-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELonger%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20married%20people%20wondering%20whether%20they%20actually%20want%20to%20spend%20their%20now-extended%20golden%20years%20with%20some%20not-so-golden%20feelings%20about%20the%20person%20next%20to%20them.%20A%20growing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-husband-gray-divorce-political-beliefs-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20over%2050%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20over%2065%20%E2%80%94%20are%20deciding%20that%20they%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20face%20of%20divorce%20has%20a%20lot%20more%20wrinkles%20and%20gray%20hair%20than%20it%20used%20to%2C%20and%20that%20brings%20with%20it%20a%20fresh%20set%20of%20financial%20calculations%20and%20complications.%20The%20challenge%20isn't%20just%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20kids%20and%20the%20house.%20It's%20dividing%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-money-mistakes-retirement-savings-prepay-debt-401k-match-vanguard-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20support%20one%20household%2C%20rewriting%20wills%20and%20trusts%2C%20and%20overhauling%20estate%20plans.%20It's%20also%20digging%20up%2025-year-old%20paperwork%20and%20worrying%20about%20what%20happens%20to%20your%20inheritance%20if%20your%2070-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-parents-divorced-i-thought-dad-didnt-love-me-anymore-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDad%20dives%20into%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%20No.%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20families%2C%20a%20late-in-life%20split%20can%20be%20a%20financial%20quagmire.%20As%20the%20US%20enters%20the%20largest%20intergenerational%20wealth%20transfer%20in%20history%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgray-divorce-attorney-insights-separation-when-older%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egray%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20quietly%20reroute%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20and%20reshape%20the%20retirement%20many%20people%20have%20envisioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20they're%20high%20net%20worth%20or%20if%20they%20have%20fewer%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Susan%20Guthrie%2C%20a%20divorce%20attorney%20and%20mediator%20based%20in%20Chicago%20and%20the%20host%20of%20the%20Divorce%20%26amp%3B%20Beyond%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20talking%20about%20a%20lifetime%20of%20creation%20being%20completely%20upended%20late%20in%20the%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-attorney-shares-four-common-mistakes-couples-do-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edivorce%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20America%20peaked%20at%2022.6%20per%201%2C000%20married%20women%20in%201980%20and%20has%20generally%20declined%20since%20then%2C%20hitting%2014.2%20per%201%2C000%20in%202024.%20Break%20it%20down%20by%20age%20group%2C%20however%2C%20and%20the%20picture%20shifts%3A%20Divorce%20has%20fallen%20among%20people%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s%20since%201990%2C%20but%20for%20people%20over%2050%2C%20it's%20doubled%2C%20and%20for%20those%20over%2065%2C%20it's%20tripled.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-and-melinda-gates-divorce-gray-divorce-trend-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOlder%20people%20still%20get%20divorced%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20lower%20rates%20than%20younger%20people%2C%20but%20nowadays%2C%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20divorces%20involve%20adults%20over%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-generation-working-not-retiring-selling-homes-miellnnials-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebaby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Elove%20%3C%2Fem%3Eleaving%20their%20spouses%3F%20Not%20entirely%2C%20but%20experts%20say%20the%20reasons%20for%20this%20surge%20in%20silver%20splits%20are%20tough%20to%20pin%20down.%20Longer%20life%20expectancies%20mean%20the%20prospect%20of%20being%20in%20an%20unhappy%20marriage%20for%20a%20longer%20period%20can%20be%20daunting.%20Now%20that%20most%20middle-class%20households%20have%20two%20incomes%2C%20both%20partners%20may%20feel%20they%20have%20greater%20financial%20independence%20to%20take%20a%20leap.%20The%20stigma%20around%20divorce%20has%20declined%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20exact%20combination%20of%20motives%2C%20divorce%20attorneys%20say%20they've%20seen%20an%20uptick%20of%20older%20people%20showing%20up%20in%20their%20offices.%20Frank%20Perrone%2C%20the%20cochair%20of%20the%20matrimonial%20law%20practice%20at%20Tarter%20Krinsky%20%26amp%3B%20Drogin%20in%20New%20York%2C%20says%20he's%20working%20on%20two%20gray%20divorce%20cases%2C%20including%20one%20where%20the%20parties%20are%20in%20their%2080s.%20The%20wife%20wants%20to%20go%20out%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-give-grandkids-money-without-sacrificing-retirement-savings-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etravel%20with%20her%20grandkids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20spend%20money%2C%20while%20the%20husband%20doesn't%20want%20to%20leave%20the%20house.%20The%20conflict%20has%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20animosity%20between%20the%20pair%2C%20so%20they've%20decided%20to%20go%20their%20separate%20ways%20and%20split%20everything%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20sad%2C%26quot%3B%20Perrone%20says%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Beverybody%20deserves%20to%20try%20to%20be%20happy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDivorce%20is%20always%20messy%2C%20but%20the%20logistics%20of%20it%20after%20decades%20together%20can%20feel%20disastrous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20younger%20couples%2C%20divorce%20tends%20to%20focus%20on%20child%20custody%20and%20support%2C%20alimony%2C%20and%20what%20happens%20to%20the%20house.%20Because%20people%20are%20early%20or%20mid-career%2C%20they%20have%20more%20runway%20to%20rebuild%20their%20assets.%20For%20older%20people%2C%20their%20high-earning%20years%20are%20largely%20behind%20them%2C%20and%20if%20one%20spouse%20hasn't%20been%20working%20for%20years%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20jumping%20back%20into%20the%20workforce%20is%20daunting.%20There's%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20divvy%20up%20and%20unwind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20major%20issues%20often%20focus%20on%20income%2C%20retirement%20assets%2C%20pensions%2C%20401(k)s%2C%20annuities.%20The%20biggest%20asset%20may%20not%20be%20the%20house%20anymore.%20It's%20more%20likely%20the%20retirement%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20Perrone%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20the%20end%20of%20the%20marriage%2C%20it's%20basically%2C%20especially%20in%20long-term%20marriages%2C%20restructuring%20almost%20an%20entire%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post-divorce%20math%20is%20often%20brutal%3A%20A%20single-person%20household%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmonthly-expenses-single-person-rent-taxes-living-alone-zillow-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emuch%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20run%20than%20a%20two-person%20household.%20Retirement%20accounts%20are%20slashed%2C%20and%20newly%20single%20Americans%20may%20have%20to%20reevaluate%20how%20they'll%20spend%20their%20time%20and%20money%20in%20their%20later%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGray%20divorce%20tends%20to%20hit%20women%20harder%20financially.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC8599059%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20shows%3C%2Fa%3E%20women%20experience%20a%2045%25%20decline%20in%20their%20standard%20of%20living%20compared%20to%20a%2021%25%20decline%20for%20men.%20While%20times%20have%20changed%2C%20many%20women%20still%20spend%20years%20at%20home%20caring%20for%20their%20children%2C%20which%20can%20dampen%20their%20earnings%20prospects%20and%20career%20advancement%20even%20if%20they%20do%20stay%20in%20the%20workforce.%20They%20also%20have%20longer%20life%20expectancies%2C%20which%20may%20mean%20they%20ultimately%20need%20more%20money%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESharon%20Klein%2C%20president%20of%20family%20wealth%20at%20Wilmington%20Trust%20in%20New%20York%20and%20the%20head%20of%20its%20divorce%20advisory%20practice%2C%20says%20that%20lingering%20traditional%20gender%20roles%20mean%20that%20women%20sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgot-divorced-knew-nothing-about-finances-job-what-to-do-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20a%20clear%20picture%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20families'%20finances%20or%20even%20have%20credit%20histories.%20They%20need%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20managing%20their%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20need%20to%20get%20educated%20about%20what%20they%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Klein%20says.%20They're%20often%20inclined%20to%20lean%20on%20friends%20and%20family%20who've%20been%20through%20similar%20experiences%2C%20and%20while%20that%20support%20is%20invaluable%2C%20those%20networks%20aren't%20equipped%20to%20handle%20the%20administrative%20nightmare%20of%20a%20late-life%20split.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20tax%20issues%2C%20legal%20issues%2C%20investment%20decisions%2C%20making%20decisions%20too%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELaws%20around%20how%20assets%20are%20divvied%20up%20vary%20state%20by%20state%2C%20and%20every%20divorce%20is%20unique.%20But%20couples%20often%20underestimate%20how%20many%20moving%20parts%20there%20will%20be%3A%20taxes%2C%20illiquid%20assets%2C%20estate%20planning%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20lots%20of%20little%20bugaboos%20and%20caveats%2C%20whatever%20you%20want%20to%20call%20them%2C%20that%20most%20people%20don't%20know%20to%20look%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeff%20Judge%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchesapeakefp.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChesapeake%20Financial%20Planners%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20may%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-does-it-cost-to-make-a-will%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eupdate%20their%20wills%3C%2Fa%3E%20post-divorce%20to%20remove%20their%20former%20spouses%20and%20not%20realize%20that%20there%20are%20other%20accounts%20whose%20beneficiaries%20also%20need%20to%20be%20updated%E2%80%94think%20trusts%2C%20401(k)s%2C%20life%20insurance.%20Or%2C%20they'll%20forget%20to%20change%20powers%20of%20attorney%2C%20and%20no%20one%20wants%20their%20ex%20deciding%20whether%20to%20pull%20the%20plug%20at%20the%20hospital.%20People%20believe%20that%20they%20split%20assets%20fairly%20upon%20separating%2C%20only%20to%20find%20out%20later%20that%20because%20of%20different%20tax%20liabilities%20on%20different%20assets%2C%20they%20wound%20up%20getting%20the%20short%20end%20of%20the%20stick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20once%20worked%20with%20a%20woman%20who%2C%20years%20after%20her%20divorce%2C%20realized%20that%20their%20%26quot%3Bequal%26quot%3B%20split%20was%20not%20so%20equal%20because%20she'd%20gotten%20accounts%20with%20a%20higher%20tax%20burden%20than%20her%20husband.%20He%20also%20recalls%20a%20client%20who%20didn't%20realize%20until%20after%20her%20husband%20died%20that%20he'd%20never%20changed%20the%20beneficiary%20of%20his%20life%20insurance%20policy.%20Hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20went%20directly%20to%20his%20ex-wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20common%20in%20a%20gray%20divorce%20for%20them%20to%20have%20left%20assets%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20ex%2C%20even%20if%20they've%20been%20divorced%20a%20long%20time%20and%20even%20if%20they%20paid%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20during%20the%20divorce%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Craig%20Parker%2C%20assistant%20general%20counsel%20of%20Trust%20%26amp%3B%20Will%2C%20a%20website%20that%20helps%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedicaid-estate-planning-dad-home-made-me-fix-my-own-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eestate%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20estate%20plan%20is%20a%20separate%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20all%20sorts%20of%20novel%20hiccups%20that%20come%20up%20in%20later-in-life%20divorces.%20Parties%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20prove%20that%20inherited%20property%20is%20only%20theirs%20because%20they%20no%20longer%20have%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20will%20that%20left%20it%20to%20them.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-get-prenup-women-assets-stock-options-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPrenuptial%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%20weren't%20as%20common%20decades%20ago%2C%20and%20even%20if%20one%20existed%2C%20people%20sometimes%20can't%20find%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdult%20children%20sometimes%20push%20their%20parents%20to%20fight%20out%20their%20divorces%20in%20court%2C%20says%20Sophie%20Spears%2C%20an%20associate%20attorney%20at%20Mosberg%20Sharma%20Stambleck%20Gross%20LLP%20in%20New%20York%2C%20instead%20of%20going%20through%20mediation%20or%20settling.%20Not%20only%20is%20that%20route%20%26quot%3Binconvenient%2C%20uncomfortable%2C%20and%20invasive%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20also%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDivorcing%20couples%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20women%20%E2%80%94%20may%20also%20not%20like%20that%20courts%20won't%20be%20amenable%20to%20including%20gifts%20to%20grandchildren%20and%20travel%20with%20family%20in%20their%20expenses%20for%20potential%20maintenance%20payments.%20Judges%20don't%20care%20about%20how%20much%20people%20want%20to%20leave%20their%20kids.%20The%20court%20bases%20its%20determinations%20only%20on%20how%20much%20the%20spouse%20needs%20for%20essentials%20such%20as%20housing%2C%20food%2C%20and%20generally%20getting%20back%20on%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlended%20families%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20when%20gray%20divorces%20get%20hairy.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20gray%20divorces%20are%20actually%20second%20marriages%2C%20says%20Michael%20Calogero%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Cohen%20Clair%20Lans%20Greifer%20%26amp%3B%20Simpson%20in%20New%20York.%20The%20parties%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20just%20focused%20on%20dividing%20those%20assets%20of%20this%20second%20marriage%2C%20but%20also%20preserving%20and%20protecting%20particular%20assets%20and%20property%20for%20their%20heirs%2C%20who%20will%20be%20different%20than%20their%20spouse's%20heirs.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20particularly%20acute%20among%20high-net-worth%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20can%20get%20even%20dicier%20if%20the%20gray%20divorce%20is%20followed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Festate-tax-qtip-trust-second-marriage-inheritance-wealth-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20gray%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20Mom%20or%20Dad%20remarries%20and%20retitles%20their%20assets%20or%20home%20to%20their%20new%20spouses%2C%20children%20may%20be%20disinherited.%20People%2C%20understandably%2C%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20their%20new%20spouse%20is%20taken%20care%20of%20in%20the%20event%20that%20they%20die%2C%20but%20their%20kids%20may%20not%20love%20that%20someone%20they're%20not%20related%20to%20winds%20up%20with%20a%20chunk%20of%20money%20they%20thought%20was%20headed%20their%20way.%20In%20many%20states%2C%20even%20if%20a%20person%20leaves%20everything%20to%20their%20children%2C%20the%20spouse%20has%20a%20legal%20right%20to%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20fortune%2C%20which%20can%20then%20be%20rerouted%20to%20their%20own%20kids.%20Families%20avoid%20planning%20around%20it%20because%20it's%20uncomfortable%2C%20and%20then%20they%20wind%20up%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20money%2C%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%2C%20when%20a%20parent%20dies%2C%20the%20children%20want%20their%20money%20immediately%2C%20and%20a%20good%20relationship%20between%20the%20children%20and%20a%20surviving%20step-parent%20can%20change%20really%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Todd%20Bornstein%2C%20a%20trust%20and%20estates%20attorney%20at%20Selzer%20Gurvitch%20Rabin%20Wertheimer%20%26amp%3B%20Polott%2C%20P.C.%20in%20Maryland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGray%20divorces%20represent%20a%20confluence%20of%20major%20life%20stressors%20all%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20broken%20relationships%2C%20retirement%2C%20estates%2C%20inheritance%2C%20declining%20health.%20It%20can%20induce%20a%20scarcity%20mindset.%20People%20have%20to%20think%20of%20everything%20from%20family%20holidays%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-planning-medicare-dementia-long-term-care-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-term%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20financial%20anxiety%20can%20hit%20even%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20wealth.%20Spuds%20Powell%2C%20managing%20director%20at%20Kayne%20Anderson%20Rudnick%20Investment%20Management%20in%20California%2C%20points%20to%20one%20client%20who%20was%20left%20with%20%2475%20million%20after%20her%20divorce.%20She%20still%20lives%20a%20%26quot%3Blife%20of%20frustration%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20because%20she%20was%20previously%20married%20to%20a%20billionaire.%20She%20wants%20to%20try%20to%20maintain%20her%20lifestyle%2C%20but%20she's%20also%20worried%20about%20overspending%20since%20she's%20no%20longer%20clued%20in%20on%20her%20ex-husband's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyer-inheritance-feels-guilty-self-made-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eestate%20plans%20for%20their%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20world%20where%20the%20exes%20are%20not%20communicating%20effectively%20with%20one%20another%2C%20how%20do%20you%20try%20to%20handle%20the%20uncertainty%20around%20what%20ultimately%20that%20means%20for%20inheritance%20for%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%20Powell%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20most%20people%20are%20not%20dealing%20with%20millions%20of%20dollars.%20They're%20just%20trying%20to%20make%20it%20through%20and%20keep%20the%20disruption%20to%20a%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValerie%20Montague%2C%20now%2069%2C%20was%2054%20when%20she%20left%20her%20marriage%20of%20two%20decades.%20Her%20husband%20was%20a%20financial%20manager%20and%20always%20handled%20the%20couple's%20accounts%2C%20so%20she%20prepared%20quietly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20get%20divorced%20suddenly%2C%26quot%3B%20Montague%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Maryland%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20started%20saving%2C%20and%20I%20told%20myself%2C%20'When%20I%20get%20to%20%2410%2C000%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20leave.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20mother%20died%20in%202009%2C%20Montague%20inherited%20the%20proceeds%20of%20a%20condo%20sale%20and%20a%20life%20insurance%20policy.%20She%20used%20it%20as%20a%20financial%20life%20raft%20to%20rent%20an%20apartment%20in%20the%20same%20school%20district%20so%20that%20her%20two%20teenage%20daughters%20could%20finish%20high%20school%20undisturbed.%20She%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20her%20job%20soon%20after%2C%20however%2C%20and%20spent%20six%20months%20unemployed%20before%20landing%20a%20new%2C%20lower-paying%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMontague%20and%20her%20ex%20agreed%20to%20wait%20to%20sell%20the%20house%20until%20after%20both%20of%20their%20daughters%20graduated%20from%20college%2C%20so%20they%20could%20use%20equity%20lines%20of%20credit%20to%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fhow-to-pay-for-college%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epay%20for%20tuition%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20meant%20that%20the%20most%20difficult%20part%20of%20their%20divorce%20came%20years%20later%2C%20when%20the%20house%20finally%20went%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20argued%20over%20every%20little%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%20%E2%80%94%20the%20inspection%2C%20the%20contract%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20after%20she%20moved%20out%20he'd%20finally%20taken%20out%20a%20loan%20for%20the%20kitchen%20renovation%20she'd%20wanted%20for%20years.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20to%20deal%20with%20him%20so%20much%20during%20that%20period%20was%20very%20stressful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sale%20closed%20shortly%20after%20her%20youngest%20daughter%20finished%20college%20in%202015%2C%20and%20Montague%20used%20the%20proceeds%20to%20buy%20her%20current%20condo%20in%202016%20%E2%80%94%20five%20years%20after%20her%20divorce%20was%20finalized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMontague%20retired%20last%20fall%2C%20but%20she%20still%20runs%20a%20side%20business%20helping%20people%20get%20their%20financial%20affairs%20in%20order.%20It's%20inspired%20by%20her%20experience%20managing%20her%20estate%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20her%20divorce.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20believe%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20divorced%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bplan%20for%20the%20financial%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-divorce-boom-reshaping-retirement-savings-inheritance-millennials-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782807481