re.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%20dispatches%20from%20Ukraine%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-robots-are-surging-into-the-kill-zone-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkraine's%20war%20robots%20are%20surging%20into%20the%20kill%20zone%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-troops-lose-days-getting-into-kill-zone-most-vulnerable-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20troops%20are%20losing%20days%20just%20getting%20to%20their%20positions%20in%20the%20kill%20zone.%20It's%20when%20they're%20most%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-turns-heavy-bombers-into-supply-drones-for-dangerous-logistics-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkraine%20is%20turning%20heavy%20bomber%20drones%20into%20supply%20haulers%20as%20front-line%20logistics%20become%20too%20dangerous%20for%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStatistically%20speaking%2C%20older%20people%20usually%20have%20a%20harder%20time%2C%20especially%20if%20they've%20never%20played%20video%20games%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Radio%20said.%20By%20contrast%2C%20teenagers%20with%20this%20experience%20can%20master%20the%20course%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20days%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae061271-39f3-43d3-bd3d-6d4ba13e3795%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%2080%25%20of%20drone%20students%20graduate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20month%2C%20roughly%20250%20students%20participate%20in%20the%20basic%20FPV%20course.%20Those%20in%20the%20daytime%20session%20train%20for%20six%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20six%20days%20a%20week.%20There's%20another%20held%20in%20the%20evening%20for%20people%20who%20have%20work%20or%20school%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20only%20three%20hours%20a%20night%20but%20goes%20for%2010%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Business%20Insider%20visited%20the%20academy%20in%20May%2C%20students%20were%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20their%20final%20day%20of%20the%20basic%20course.%20It's%20a%20tough%20program%2C%20and%20not%20everyone%20makes%20it%20through%3B%20only%2080%25%20of%20students%20graduate%2C%20receiving%20a%20certificate%20showing%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-pilot-score-board-log-800000-hits-russia-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equalified%20drone%20pilots%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20who%20fail%20the%20final%20exam%20can%20try%20again%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20instructional%20portion%20of%20the%20course%20is%20held%20in%20a%20temporary%20module-turned-classroom%20inside%20the%20large%20warehouse%2C%20where%20students%20learn%20the%20basics%20of%20FPVs%20%E2%80%94%20including%20how%20they%20are%20built%20and%20how%20they%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20practice%20flying%20on%20computer%20simulators%20before%20they%20hit%20the%20obstacle%20course%20with%207-inch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussians-turn-recon-drone-orlan-mothership-fpv-quadcopters-flash-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equadcopters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20standard%20size%20for%20FPV%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20additional%20modules%20in%20the%20warehouse%20that%20serve%20as%20ground%20control%20stations%2C%20allowing%20multiple%20students%20to%20fly%20through%20the%20obstacle%20courses%20simultaneously.%20While%20it's%20possible%20to%20pilot%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-leopard-tank-crew-train-varjo-fynd-headsets-mixed-reality-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtual%20reality%20headset%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20work%20with%20computer%20screens%2C%20allowing%20students%20to%20work%20in%20teams%20while%20instructors%20watch%20their%20moves%20from%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20student%20pilots%20a%20drone.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d3a82360acd489560b30d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20basic%20FPV%20course%20costs%20%24180%20for%20Ukrainians.%20Foreigners%2C%20who%20make%20up%205%25%20of%20students%2C%20pay%20twice%20that.%3Cp%3EJake%20Epstein%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20usually%20begin%20working%20on%20the%20obstacle%20course%20of%20tires%20and%20metal%20hoops%20on%20the%20second%20or%20third%20day%2C%20after%20completing%20simulator%20exercises.%20To%20graduate%2C%20they%20must%20show%20they%20can%20handle%20the%20basics%20that%20matter%20most%20in%20combat%3A%20takeoff%2C%20hovering%2C%20flying%20through%20at%20least%20three%20obstacles%2C%20and%20landing.%20To%20wage%20war%20effectively%2C%20they'll%20want%20to%20continue%20honing%20their%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-drone-racers-are-fast-not-good-slow-hunting-training-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPiloting%20an%20FPV%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20too%20difficult%2C%20Sante%20said%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit%20takes%20time%20to%20get%20adapted%20to%20the%20drone%20controller%20and%20the%20drone%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20both%20of%20which%20are%20highly%20sensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20getting%20used%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Radio%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20understand%20how%20it%20works.%20Your%20brain%20has%20to%20build%20those%20neural%20connections%2C%20and%20that's%20probably%20the%20hardest%20part.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20hardest%20thing%20in%20FPV%20piloting%20is%20flying%20very%20slowly%20or%20hovering%20in%20one%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FPVs%20lack%20a%20stabilization%20feature%2C%20he%20said.%20They%20can't%20hover%20in%20place%20at%20the%20push%20of%20a%20button%2C%20so%20pilots%20have%20to%20constantly%20make%20little%20movements%20to%20keep%20the%20drones%20from%20crashing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20basic%20course%20focuses%20on%20teaching%20pilots%20that%20sense%20of%20control%2C%20said%20Tokyo%2C%20an%20instructor%20who%20goes%20by%20her%20call%20sign.%20Students%20learn%20to%20hover%2C%20make%20tight%20turns%2C%20and%20handle%20practical%20issues%20such%20as%20signal%20loss.%20Later%20in%20their%20training%2C%20they%20may%20learn%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-drone-operators-not-spared-war-horrors-are-top-targets-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunt%20moving%20targets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20teaching%20them%20to%20fly%20slowly%20because%20that%20means%20you%20can%20fly%20much%20longer%20distances%20because%20your%20battery%20wouldn't%20discharge%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20Tokyo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Students%20during%20the%20instructional%20portion.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d3c33360acd489560b336%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20program%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20classroom-style%20instruction%20and%20flight%20training%20through%20an%20obstacle%20course.%3Cp%3EJake%20Epstein%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224881b845-949a-40cd-9744-c9e6e08d0930%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUkraine%20is%20constantly%20updating%20its%20courses%20to%20meet%20new%20battlefield%20challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKillhouse%20is%20part%20of%20Ukraine's%20attempt%20to%20turn%20battlefield%20experience%20into%20something%20repeatable%3A%20train%20pilots%2C%20absorb%20new%20lessons%20from%20the%20front%2C%20update%20the%20course%2C%20and%20send%20those%20lessons%20back%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20recently%20signed%20drone%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-war-startups-pushing-to-meet-nato-standards-win-deals-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecurity%20deals%20with%20NATO%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20countries%2C%20and%20it%20has%20sent%20specialists%20abroad%20to%20train%20foreign%20militaries%20in%20drone%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmerops-middle-east-iran-drones-shaheds-surveyor-us-military-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecounter-drone%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadio%20said%20discussions%20are%20underway%20with%20several%20countries%2C%20including%20some%20NATO%20members%2C%20to%20launch%20Killhouse%20courses%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFresh%20battlefield%20data%20has%20led%20to%20improvements%20in%20the%20courses%2C%20and%20that%20constant%20updating%20is%20central%20to%20the%20academy's%20purpose.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-himars-mid-range-drones-strike-atacms-russia-analysts-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDrone%20warfare%20has%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E%20significantly%20in%20the%20two%20years%20since%20Killhouse%20launched%2C%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20change%2C%20forcing%20instructors%20to%20adjust%20the%20course%20so%20pilots%20are%20not%20learning%20tactics%20already%20overtaken%20by%20evolutions%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadio%20said%20Killhouse%20is%20always%20watching%20what's%20happening%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-image-russian-drone-launch-site-near-ukraine-front-line-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20front%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20through%20the%20eyes%20of%20its%20instructors%20with%20combat%20experience.%20Sometimes%20this%20means%20making%20adjustments%2C%20such%20as%20creating%20harder%20obstacle%20courses%20to%20challenge%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drone%20navigates%20through%20an%20obstacle.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d3bd7a25092c74cc9f1c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrone%20warfare%20has%20changed%20significantly%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20and%20the%20Killhouse%20is%20constantly%20updating%20its%20program.%3Cp%3EJake%20Epstein%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20situation%20changes%20constantly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFiber%20optics%20appeared%2C%20the%20role%20of%20ground%20robotic%20systems%20is%20becoming%20more%20visible%20and%20more%20important%2C%20and%20we%2C%20of%20course%2C%20adapt%20to%20the%20modern%20conditions%20of%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20shifts%20in%20the%20war%20this%20year%20has%20been%20Ukraine's%20push%20to%20replace%20humans%20with%20drones%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-turns-heavy-bombers-into-supply-drones-for-dangerous-logistics-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20logistics%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20has%20made%20flying%20skills%20important%20beyond%20attack%20missions.%20Drones%20are%20now%20part%20of%20how%20Ukrainian%20forces%20move%20ammunition%2C%20food%2C%20water%2C%20and%20other%20supplies%20through%20areas%20where%20sending%20people%20can%20be%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLogistics%20today%20can't%20be%20executed%20without%20drones%20%E2%80%94%20ground%20drones%20or%20flying%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20Sante%20said.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20drones%2C%20you're%20dead.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20role%20of%20drones%20could%20change%20again%20as%20the%20war%20evolves%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20vital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainians-want-to-fly-drones-first-survive-killhouse-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782807421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42a57de218c3b62535ed16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainians-want-to-fly-drones-first-survive-killhouse-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20drones%20radically%20change%20how%20wars%20are%20fought%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20putting%20would-be%20pilots%20through%20a%20test%20of%20nerves%20and%20skill%20before%20sending%20them%20to%20fight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jepstein%40businessinsider.com%20(Jake%20Epstein)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Congress%20delegation%20Ayodhya%20visit%20row%3A%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20slams%20party%2C%20says%20it%20is%20'leaning%20on%20lies'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782807137000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-132088266%2Cimgsize-87845.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fcongress-delegation-ayodhya-visit-row-yogi-adityanath-slams-party-says-it-is-leaning-on-lies%2Farticleshow%2F132088244.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Uttar%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20sharply%20criticized%20the%20Congress%20over%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20donation%20row%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20hypocrisy%20and%20past%20anti-devotee%20actions.%20He%20stated%20that%20those%20who%20once%20opposed%20Lord%20Ram%20are%20now%20eager%20to%20visit%20Ayodhya.%20This%20comes%20as%20the%20Congress%20alleged%20house%20arrests%20of%20its%20leaders%2C%20including%20state%20chief%20Ajay%20Rai%2C%20who%20planned%20to%20visit%20Ayodhya%20amid%20the%20embezzlement%20controversy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20AI%20data%20center%20suing%20for%20Colorado%20River%20water%20highlights%20a%20bigger%20question%3A%20Who%20should%20get%20the%20West's%20water%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20shrinking%20Salton%20Sea%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42c743e218c3b62535eeb8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222970%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrought%20has%20long%20been%20a%20challenge%20in%20California's%20Imperial%20Valley.%3Cp%3EAllen%20J.%20Schaben%20%2F%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20data%20center%20developer%20in%20California%20is%20suing%20for%20access%20to%20Colorado%20River%20water.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20developer%20wants%20to%20use%20water%20allocated%20to%20farmland%20and%20use%20it%20for%20cooling%20instead.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWater%20experts%20and%20local%20advocates%20say%20it%20raises%20bigger%20questions%20about%20how%20water%20should%20be%20used.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20developer%20behind%20what%20would%20be%20California's%20largest%20AI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-center-near-me-location-tracker-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20suing%20for%20access%20to%20Colorado%20River%20water%2C%20the%20threatened%20source%20of%20freshwater%20for%2040%20million%20people%20and%20the%20subject%20of%20countless%20disputes%20over%20water%20use%20in%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20this%20month%20by%20Imperial%20Valley%20Computer%20Manufacturing%2C%20says%20the%20company%20needs%20access%20to%20287%20million%20gallons%20of%20water%20for%20the%20330-megawatt%20data%20center.%20If%20the%20proposed%20project%20in%20Southern%20California's%20Imperial%20Valley%20is%20built%2C%20it%20would%20be%20the%20largest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ai-data-center-power-electricity-use-consumption-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20data%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%20after%20the%20Imperial%20Irrigation%20District%2C%20a%20local%20agency%20that%20delivers%20Colorado%20River%20water%20in%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%2C%20denied%20the%20company's%20request%20for%20water%20for%20the%20project.%20It%20also%20comes%20as%20communities%20across%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-center-owner-calls-out-google-project-iowa-palo-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20back%20against%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Colorado%20River%20is%20the%20only%20source%20of%20freshwater%20in%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%2C%20which%20has%20long%20faced%20drought%20and%20water%20supply%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20developer%2C%20Sebastian%20Rucci%2C%20said%20the%20project%20would%20not%20add%20to%20demand%20on%20the%20river%20overall%20because%20the%20company%20would%20fallow%2C%20or%20stop%20irrigating%2C%20nearby%20farmland%20and%20use%20that%20water%20to%20cool%20the%20data%20center%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERucci%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20proposal%20would%20have%20%26quot%3Bzero%20impact%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20data%20center%20would%20not%20require%20any%20additional%20allocation%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-western-states-disagree-colorado-river-cuts-proposal-borrowed-water-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColorado%20River%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20its%20water%20demand%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20a%20160-acre%20farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20experts%20and%20local%20advocates%20say%20the%20case%20raises%20a%20bigger%20question%20than%20how%20much%20water%20a%20single%20data%20center%20should%20use%3A%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-data-centers-are-deepening-the-water-crisis-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20becomes%20scarcer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20new%20industries%20increase%20demand%2C%20should%20water%20historically%20used%20for%20farming%20be%20redirected%20to%20power%20the%20AI%20boom%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c17050c2-5ec1-4e94-9f5e-a4ade54a5b86%5C%22%3EMoving%20water%20from%20farming%20to%20data%20centers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EImperial%20Valley's%20identity%20has%20been%20tied%20to%20farming%2C%20with%20cattle%2C%20alfalfa%2C%20lettuce%2C%20and%20spinach%20among%20its%20top%20commodities.%20John%20Fleck%2C%20a%20writer%20and%20water%20policy%20expert%20at%20the%20University%20of%20New%20Mexico%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Btaking%20land%20out%20of%20agricultural%20production%20to%20use%20for%20other%20things%20is%20a%20values%20question%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20small%20amount.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Horseshoe%20Bend%2C%20a%20horseshoe-shaped%20incised%20meander%20of%20the%20Colorado%20River%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42c7de360acd489560d211%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Colorado%20River%20is%20the%20source%20of%20freshwater%20for%2040%20million%20people.%3Cp%3EThomas%20O'Neill%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Cohen%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Pacific%20Institute%20focusing%20on%20Colorado%20River%20Basin%20water%20use%2C%20said%20the%20issue%20is%20not%20necessarily%20the%20amount%20of%20water%2C%20but%20rather%20the%20developer's%20plan%20to%20access%20farmland%2C%20dry%20it%20up%2C%20and%20reallocate%20it%20for%20industrial%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20resistance%20in%20any%20agricultural%20community%20to%20'buy%20and%20dry'%20because%20that's%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERucci%20said%20his%20company%20has%20a%20contract%20to%20purchase%20the%20land%20and%20water%20assignments%20from%20farmers.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20pursued%20this%20strategy%20after%20his%20proposals%20to%20use%20reclaimed%20water%20were%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20individual%20landowners%20may%20profit%20from%20the%20practice%2C%20taking%20farmland%20out%20of%20production%20can%20have%20cascading%20effects%20in%20agricultural%20communities%2C%20including%20fewer%20farm-related%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImperial%20Valley's%20economy%20has%20long%20relied%20on%20Colorado%20River%20agriculture.%20If%20it%20weren't%20for%20that%20part%20of%20the%20country%20around%20Imperial%20and%20Yuma%2C%20Arizona%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20in%20America%20could%20afford%20a%20salad%20in%20February%2C%26quot%3B%20Rhett%20Larson%2C%20a%20water-law%20expert%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarson%20said%20that%20while%20farmers%20may%20make%20money%20selling%20land%20or%20water%20rights%2C%20the%20people%20who%20are%20often%20hurt%20are%20the%20fertilizer%20salesmen%2C%20tractor%20repairmen%2C%20teachers%2C%20dry%20cleaners%2C%20or%20anyone%20in%20these%20rural%20communities%20who%20doesn't%20have%20land%20or%20water%20rights%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERucci%20said%20the%20data%20center%20would%20bring%20major%20economic%20benefits%20to%20Imperial%20County%2C%20including%201%2C688%20construction%20jobs%2C%20over%20a%20hundred%20permanent%20jobs%2C%20and%20an%20estimated%20%242.95%20billion%20in%20economic%20improvement%20over%2030%20years%2C%20citing%20an%20independent%20economic%20study%20prepared%20for%20the%20county.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEconomic%20diversification%20is%20exactly%20what%20the%20area%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20Rucci%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%2C%20pointing%20to%20Imperial%20County's%20high%20unemployment.%20The%20county's%20unemployment%20rate%20was%20about%2017%25%20as%20of%20May%2C%20according%20to%20state%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20farm%20field%20and%20tractor.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42c830360acd489560d215%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECalifornia's%20Imperial%20Valley%20is%20a%20major%20agricultural%20hub.%3Cp%3EAllen%20J.%20Schaben%20%2F%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22933ca041-3cfd-4113-9e1b-94f6636f55dc%5C%22%3EWho%20makes%20decisions%20about%20water%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Reyes%2C%20an%20Imperial%20Valley%20resident%20and%20the%20executive%20director%20at%20the%20advocacy%20organization%20Los%20Amigos%20de%20la%20Comunidad%2C%20said%20he's%20concerned%20the%20lawsuit%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20circumvent%20the%20Imperial%20Irrigation%20District%20(IDD)%2C%20a%20publicly%20owned%20utility%20governed%20by%20an%20elected%20board.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-californias-on-site-water-recycling-can-boost-water-conservation-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWater%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20area%20have%20long%20been%20held%20in%20trust%20by%20the%20IID%2C%20rather%20than%20individual%20landowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReyes%20said%20the%20developer's%20plan%20%26quot%3Braised%20a%20huge%20red%20flag%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20could%20involve%20a%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20deal%20with%20a%20landowner%20and%20then%20use%20it%20for%20his%20own%20purpose.%26quot%3B%20He%20sees%20it%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20circumvent%20the%20IID%20and%20give%20landowners%20more%20power%20over%20water%2C%20some%20of%20whom%2C%20he%20says%2C%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bfarm%20water%20instead%20of%20farmland%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20or%20sell%20water%20intended%20for%20farming%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebecause%20it%20can%20be%20more%20lucrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERucci%20rejected%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20circumvent%20IID's%20control%20and%20said%20farmers%20have%20the%20right%20under%20state%20law%20to%20assign%20water%2C%20and%20that%20the%20proposals%20would%20not%20require%20%26quot%3Ba%20single%20additional%20drop%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20Colorado%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarson%20said%20the%20case%20shows%20why%20water%20fights%20in%20the%20West%20are%20rarely%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolaroid-anti-ai-data-centers-water-ad-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20conservation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20will%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20we%20need%20to%20conserve%20water%2C'%20but%20they'll%20often%20stop%20at%20that%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20ask%20another%20question%2C%20which%20is%2C%20'conserve%20it%20for%20what%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20water%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efarms%20to%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20a%20choice%20some%20communities%20make%2C%20Larson%20said%2C%20but%20there%20will%20be%20tradeoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Colorado%20River%20basin%20has%20to%20decide%20what%20we%20want%20to%20be%20when%20we%20grow%20up%20and%20what%20it%20will%20take%20to%20get%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20enough%20water%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20great%20things.%20But%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20water%20to%20do%20every%20good%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-center-lawsuit-california-imperial-valley-colorado-river-water-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782807062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42c87e360acd489560d216%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-center-lawsuit-california-imperial-valley-colorado-river-water-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20developer%20of%20what%20would%20be%20the%20largest%20AI%20data%20center%20in%20California%20wants%20to%20use%20Colorado%20River%20water%20currently%20tied%20to%20farmland.