he%20show%2C%20run%20by%20Dropout%20%E2%80%94%20a%20media%20company%20spun%20off%20from%20the%20former%20CollegeHumor%20%E2%80%94%20involves%20Mulligan%20or%20other%20game%20masters%20weaving%20a%20fantastical%20tale%20of%20adventure%20and%20magic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMulligan%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20hours%20long%20games%2C%20at%20stadiums%20and%20in%20the%20show's%20recorded%20form%20without%20Skye%20Smith%2C%20his%20lore%20keeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Business%20Insider%20asked%20Smith%20to%20sum%20up%20her%20work%2C%20she%20described%20herself%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BGoogle%2C%20or%20Wikipedia%2C%20for%20'Dimension%2020.'%26quot%3B%20She's%20in%20charge%20of%20knowing%20the%20show's%20encyclopedic%2C%20sprawling%20history%2C%20from%20timelines%20to%20factoids%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20her%20boss%20and%20his%20players%20keep%20it%20all%20straight%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235a78d00-3bae-45e5-81d2-436022ff361a%5C%22%3EThe%20game%20master's%20right-hand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShows%20like%20%26quot%3BDimension%2020%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatt-mercer-brennan-lee-mulligan-critical-role-dimension-20-collaboration-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BCritical%20Role%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20need%20lore%20keepers%20for%20one%20reason%3A%20There's%20just%20too%20much%20to%20remember.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-cco-matt-mercer-top-tip-cope-with-burnout-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BCritical%20Role%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20streamed%20multi-year%20tabletop%20games%20for%20hundreds%20of%20episodes%2C%20totaling%20thousands%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%26quot%3BDimension%2020%26quot%3B%20has%20shorter%20seasons%2C%20the%20game%20master%20leans%20on%20an%20assistant%20to%20ensure%20he%20gets%20the%20plot%20points%20and%20facts%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20filming%20day%20for%20me%20is%20very%20different%20than%20a%20regular%2010-to-6%20workday.%20It's%20always%20going%20to%20be%20at%20least%20a%2012-hour%20workday.%20I%20get%20to%20set%20the%20same%20time%20as%20our%20GM%2C%20Brennan.%20And%20then%20I%20stay%20until%20pretty%20much%20the%20very%20last%20person%20has%20left%20set%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDimension%2020%26quot%3B%20films%20multiple%20episodes%20a%20day%2C%20and%20she%20and%20Mulligan%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20Slack%26quot%3B%20going%20as%20they%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20takes%20notes%20on%20the%20ongoing%20game%2C%20then%20fields%20questions%20called%20to%20her%20off-camera.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed0e7710-5844-48da-a6fc-02d6e11e2f2c%5C%22%3EStaying%20organized%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20keep%20track%20of%20evolving%20lore%2C%20Smith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairtables-ceo-wants-staff-take-time-off-work-play-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euses%20Airtable%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20most%20of%20her%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20uses%20some%20good%20old-fashioned%20sticky%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20usually%20have%20a%20printout%20of%20either%20the%20materials%20that%20they%20use%20at%20the%20table%20for%20the%20game%20that%20we%20play%2C%20or%20a%20visual%20of%20the%20world%20we're%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20always%20have%20a%20notebook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20lorekeeping%2C%20Smith%20is%20involved%20in%20the%20creative%20process%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdimension-20-new-season-misfits-and-magic-aabria-iyengar-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BDimension%2020's%26quot%3B%20new%20seasons%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20pitching%20and%20ideation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20get%20to%20know%20what's%20cooking%20really%20early%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22548ca9cc-910e-4f7e-9a50-b4a3f84f14a9%5C%22%3EThe%20AI%20question%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20her%20job%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-no-ai-legend-of-vox-machina-fourth-season-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eendangered%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20note-takers%2C%20Smith%20said%20that%20her%20work%20revolves%20around%20listening%2C%20spotting%20human%20error%2C%20and%20understanding%20the%20lore%20of%20the%20fantasy%20world%20being%20made%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20big%20part%20of%20this%20job%20and%20why%20it's%20important%20has%20to%20do%20with%20human%20error%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20And%20so%20fixing%20'errors'%20with%20a%20machine%20would%20never%20work%20because%20what%20you%20need%20is%20another%20human%20set%20of%20eyes%20who%20knows%20the%20pitfalls%20of%20making%20something%20creative%2C%20knows%20where%20the%20weak%20spots%20are%2C%20and%20you%20just%20can't%20train%20an%20electronic%20artificial%20intelligence%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20you%20can%20train%20human%20intuition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20added%20that%20she%20enjoys%20the%20%26quot%3Bhard%20parts%26quot%3B%20of%20her%20job%20that%20other%20people%20might%20find%20taxing%20or%20that%20they%20might%20look%20to%20robots%20to%20help%20with%2C%20such%20as%20taking%20%26quot%3Bhours%20and%20hours%20of%20notes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20double-layered%20answer%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20never%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%20as%20well%20as%20I%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20given%20the%20environmental%20effects%20of%20AI%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20even%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20try.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219b65c26-c664-45cb-80f2-fd56d31d372b%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20the%20gig%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20worked%20her%20way%20up%20to%20lore%20keeper%20from%20an%20entry-level%20role%20as%20a%20production%20assistant%20in%202023%2C%20then%20jumped%20a